reviews.title: Nice cozy dining place
reviews.text: Nice place with very good food. The menu doesn't have any gigantic special dishes but it is tasty. The location is nice and cozy. For a nice meal you've definitely come to the right place

reviews.title: How about a cup of coffee? Here you have to be
reviews.text: Delicious cup of coffee with super pastries, staff is very friendly and therefore there is very pleasant atmosphere in the restaurant

reviews.title: Nice dinner, but expensive.
reviews.text:
We go for lunch more often at the old bakery and then the price quality ratio is super. Now chosen to dine, super quality but very expensive bill. 

Very different from lunch where this is nicely proportioned. Would rather choose another restaurant for dinner on Urk next time. Furthermore, good food!

reviews.title: Escape the harbor restaurants. Great food and friendly staff
reviews.text: Very nice food and great service. Great choice of food. Mainly local things. Very friendly staff. Great choice away from the busy harbor restaurants. Very well worth the 5min walk

reviews.title: Finally hot cappuccino!!
reviews.text: Very good and finally a good hot cappuccino! You can sit there comfortably with fresh rolls! Really great! Friendly people and I will definitely come back here again!!

reviews.title: What a cake!!
reviews.text: Amazing cakes and food, served with passion and good coffee. This is all you need. Nice location for lunch, Coffee and most likely also dinner (we visited during the afternoon only).

reviews.title: Delicious bread
reviews.text: The most delicious carbohydrate free bread and rolls we've ever tasted. We bought enough for a month to freeze in at home.

reviews.title: Exquisite
reviews.text: We stopped here for some bread and also bought a small selection of pastries. Later we thoroughly enjoyed some exquisite patisserie.

reviews.title: Lovely & Cosy
reviews.text: A gorgeous cosy restaurant with a Bakery attached to it. Every day fresh baked bread and pastries, e-number free, lovely fresh roasted coffee .. just a great place to take some time for yourself and relax. Food is delicious and fresh, great combination of ingredients. Friendly service with a smile.

reviews.title: My Highlight
reviews.text: The highlight of our summer vacation: 'Mimme's Mix' cake box for the afternoon coffee brake! Must have!

reviews.title: Excellent
reviews.text:
At first glance we thought that this was just a bakery; it is but it is also so much more. It was a beautiful day so we sat outside (they have seating at the side of the bakery and at the front). As soon as we sat down a server came over and handed us the menus and took our drink order. We needed help with the language as they didn't have an English menu. That was no problem at all. We decided on an egg dish which was an omelette on a small baguette served with, in my case, bacon and cheese. Delicious! My partner had the same type of meal but had the salmon instead of the bacon. Also sensational!
We've been to Urk many times but somehow never came upon this bakery till now and cannot wait to go back. Excellent on all counts.

reviews.title: Bedankt! Ein Tip für Feinschmecker!
reviews.text:
Hello Oudebakkerij Team, dear Johanna Jonkers,
 
 
We would like to say Thank you for your delicious Dinner you served at 23.09.2017. We were on Vaccation from Germany and we were flashed by your creatings!
 
Sole / Lamp / Krokettjes and your Cheesplate where amazing….all handmade style!your are an fantastic cook! Also the Restaurant is very pretty! Wine and beer expertise also great!
 
We think lovly backward to these moments. I was great that you even on tired moment are able to do your creative handmade work! Sorry we torment you!
 
Deply respect to your work!
 
Best Food I even enjoyed in Holland!

Greetings from Germany / Hessen / Wetzlar

reviews.title: great place to have lunch, the entrance to the eatery is on the right of the building
reviews.text: We enjoyed our meal at this place. The front of the building is a normal bakery shop with pastries and bread for sale. The front right is a cooler section and if you go straight through a small door, you come into the eatery that can also be entered from the large entrance on the right of the building. A bit confusing when you are in the bakery shop. They should have put a little sign on the door that leads from the bakery shop into the eatery. But that said: the staff is very friendly and we had a great lunch. Would stop and eat here again!

articleContent.title: Celebrate the best of Osaka’s food and nightlife with Suntory

seoInfo.metaDescription: If you’ve ever found yourself standing in line for hours at a famous ramen spot in Japan, you’d probably agree that food and drinks are a big part of why we travel. It’s one of the best ways to get a glimpse into a destination's culture, traditions, and history, whether it’s through its local dishes, ingredients, or culinary customs. But if you really want to embrace local culture, there’s no better way than over a glass. Share a drink with locals, friends, and fellow travelers, and experience the camaraderie, stories, and traditions that make up the heart of a destination, forging deeper connections along the way.
